<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">

	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

	<meta name="google" content="notranslate" />
	<meta http-equiv="content-language" content="en" />

	<title><%= htmlWebpackPlugin.options.title %></title>

	<style>
		iframe#webpack-dev-server-client-overlay {
			display: none;
		}

		#editor {
			border: 1px solid #aaa;
			box-sizing: content-box;
			min-height: 100px;
			padding: 5px;
		}

		article {
			padding: 0 20px;
			display: block;
		}

		@media (min-width: 900px) {
			article {
				margin-top: 50px;
			}
		}

		section {
			background: #fff;
    		box-shadow: 0 0 1px 1px #c6e6f2;
    		margin: 0 auto;
    		max-width: 870px;
    		padding: 2em;
		}

		#help {
			min-height: 200px;

			display: flex;
			flex-direction: row;
		}

		#table {
			padding-left: 1rem;
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 50% 50%;
			grid-template-rows: repeat(10, min-content);
			justify-items: left;
			align-items: center;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body class="notranslate">
	<article>
		<section>
			<h1>Sunstar's Editor Demo</h1>
			<strong>Version 0.0.1-test1 (August 26, 2023)</strong>
			<hr>

			<div id="help">
				<div style="width: 55%;">
					<ul>
						<li>A math and rich text editor based on the Matriculation Examination Board's rich-text-editor.</li>
						<li>This is still very early in development. Expect bugs and unfinished features.</li>
						<li>The initial test release was released on August 26, 2023.</li>
						<li>You can follow the development <a href="https://github.com/SunstarVIII/editor" target="_blank">on the project's GitHub repo page</a>.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div style="width: 45%;" id="table">
					<p>Paste an image from the clipboard</p>
					<p>Ctrl-V</p>
					<p>Insert an equation using MathLive</p>
					<p>Ctrl-E</p>
					<strong>In the MathLive editor</strong>
					<p></p>
					<p>Close the math editor (deleting it if empty)</p>
					<p>Esc</p>
					<p>Continue on a new line</p>
					<p>Enter</p>
					<p>Write formulae using LaTeX</p>
					<p></p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div id="editor"></div>
		</section>
	</article>

	<footer>

	</footer>

	<%= htmlWebpackPlugin.tags.bodyTags %>

	<script async="false">
		const editor = document.querySelector('#editor');
		setTimeout(() => {
			initMistyEditor(editor, {});
		}, 1000);
	</script>
</body>
</html>